<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-22T00:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-22T00:23:00-05:00" n="1025" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1025">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16986.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-21T22:00:00-07:23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1915—10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your December 21. General Obregon is authorized to proceed to El Paso via
                            American Territory, provided he travels as civilian and unarmed. So
                            inform federal authorities on border, especially military
                            authorities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>